  "text": "The idea of using tailor-made hardware for database processing dates back at least to the late 1970s, when DeWitt explored what was called a \"database machine\" at the time [CITATION_1] . His Direct system used specialized co-processors that operated close to secondary storage and provided explicit database support in its instruction set.",
  "correct_citation": {
